}, "short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 173}, "passed": true}}, "text": "UAR Orders Reduction of Military Mission in Yemen\n\nThe head of the UAR military mission in Yemen is carrying out orders from Cairo to reduce the size of the mission.\ndo not reveal how much of a reduction is contemplated or when it will be effected. The mission, which first arrived in 1957, probably numbers around 100 men.\n\nCairo is undoubtedly aware of the Imam's displeasure over the size of the mission and the fact that it has at times interfered in Yemen's internal affairs.\n\nHe suspects that Crown Prince Badr and the UAR are collaborating. Badr used members of the mission against dissident elements responsible for disturbances at Al-Hadaydah and Taiz during the Imam's absence.\n\nthe mission has been in contact with and may have given funds to elements probably opposed to the Imam. Upon the Imam's return last month, the head of the mission anticipated the possibility that a reduction would be demanded, but told Cairo he thought it would be necessary to \"withdraw only those who are without actual work", "token_count": 173, "token_end_0based": 172, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "uar orders reduction of military mission in yemen the head of the uar military mission in yemen is carrying out orders from cairo to reduce the size of the mission do not reveal how much of a reduction is contemplated or when it will be effected the mission which first arrived in 1957 probably numbers around 100 men cairo is undoubtedly aware of the imam's displeasure over the size of the mission and the fact that it has at times interfered in yemen's internal affairs he suspects that crown prince badr and the uar are collaborating badr used members of the mission against dissident elements responsible for disturbances at al-hadaydah and taiz during the imam's absence the mission has been in contact with and may have given funds to elements probably opposed to the imam upon the imam's return last month the head of the mission anticipated the possibility that a reduction would be demanded but told cairo he thought it would be necessary to withdraw only those who are without actual work", "unred_source_page": 13}
